(brand_guide.pdf) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(GLOW BRAND IDENTITY & VISUAL GUIDELINES \(v2.4\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. BRAND VOICE AND TONE) Tj
T*
(Glow is the "Transparent Authority" in clinical skincare. Our voice is data-driven,) Tj
T*
(empathetic, and strictly anti-hype. We speak like a knowledgeable friend who happens to) Tj
T*
(be a chemist.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Direct and Transparent: We lead with active ingredients and clinical percentages) Tj
T*
(\(e.g., "15% Vitamin C" rather than "Brightening Serum"\).) Tj
T*
(- Empathetic but Scientific: Acknowledge skin struggles \(acne, aging, redness\) without) Tj
T*
(using "fear-based" marketing. We solve problems; we don't shame them.) Tj
T*
(- Concise: In ad copy, get to the benefit in the first 40 characters. Use bullet points) Tj
T*
(for efficacy data.) Tj
T*
(- Prohibited Phrases: "Miracle cure," "Instant results," "Secret formula," "Toxic-free.") Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2. COLOR PALETTE) Tj
T*
(Our palette is designed to evoke a clinical environment that feels warm and accessible.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Glow Primary White: #FFFFFF \(Backgrounds, clean space\)) Tj
T*
(- Clinical Slate: #2C3E50 \(Primary typography, heavy borders\)) Tj
T*
(- Serum Amber: #FFBF00 \(Call-to-outs, active ingredient highlighting\)) Tj
T*
(- Skin Neutral 01-04: A range of muted beiges \(#F5E6D3 to #D2B48C\) used for secondary) Tj
T*
(backgrounds.) Tj
T*
(- Action Teal: #008080 \(Primary CTA buttons only\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3. IMAGERY AND CREATIVE RULES) Tj
T*
(We prioritize "Real Skin" over "Perfect Skin." ) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Macro Textures: High-resolution shots of the product texture \(swatches, drops,) Tj
T*
(bubbles\) are our highest-performing assets. ) Tj
T*
(- Real Results: Before/After imagery must be standardized. Same lighting, same angle,) Tj
T*
("Unretouched" watermark required in Clinical Slate 10pt font.) Tj
T*
(- Diversity in Casting: Models must represent a range of Fitzpatrick skin types \(1-6\).) Tj
T*
(Avoid heavy makeup; skin should look hydrated but natural \(the "Glow"\).) Tj
T*
(- Typography in Creative: Use "Inter" \(Bold\) for headlines. Text overlays should never) Tj
T*
(cover more than 20% of the frame. Use high-contrast backgrounds for readability.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(4. AD COPY STRUCTURE) Tj
T*
(- The Hook: Lead with a specific pain point or a surprising data point \(e.g., "Why 80%) Tj
T*
(of Retinol users stop after 2 weeks"\).) Tj
T*
(- The Proof: Cite a clinical study or a specific ingredient concentration.) Tj
T*
(- The Close: Low-friction CTA. Use "Shop the Science" or "Start Your Routine" instead of) Tj
T*
("Buy Now.") Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(5. LOGO USAGE) Tj
T*
(- The Glow wordmark must have a minimum clear space equal to the height of the 'G'.) Tj
ET
endstream
